[SAY] The entire screen refreshed. Everything re-rendered cleanly. You might not notice anything when the display is already correct.
[SAY] You'll need this when a background process prints to your terminal and messes up Vim's display. Or when you resize your terminal window and things look off.
[SAY] Some people also use colon redraw exclamation mark, which does the same thing from command mode.
